<CORRECTION>
<P>
IMPERFECTIONS 
</P>
<P>
OK, there were a few gaffes in our Sneaks '89. It is Edward S. Feldman -- not 
Ed Pressman -- who is producing "Wired" with Charles Meeker. The Francis Ford 
Coppola-directed segment of "New York Stories" stars newcomer Heather McComb, 
not Coppola's daughter, Sofia. Sofia co-wrote the script with her father and 
also designed the costumes and titles. Merrin Holt and Ken Krauss are the 
writers of the comedy "Buy and Cell," not director Robert Boris. And the 
vampire picture "To Die For" -- which we labeled "distributor pending" -- will 
be distributed by Skouras Pictures in March. 
</P>
<P>
IMPERFECTIONS 
</P>
<P>
The actress in mouse makeup for "The Witches" was incorrectly identified as 
Anjelica Huston in Jan. 15's "Sneaks '89" roundup. The rodent's true identity 
was not available at press time. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
